# Commit messages

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/): `type(scope): subject`

## Format

```
type(scope): imperative subject

Optional body explaining why, not what.
```

- **subject**: lowercase, imperative mood, no trailing period, ~72 chars max
- **scope**: optional; package or area (`web`, `db`, `docker`, `docs`, `cursor`)
- **body**: separate from subject with a blank line when needed

## Types

| Type | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | New behavior or MCP tool |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, config, gitignore |
| `refactor` | Code change without behavior change |
| `test` | Tests only |
| `build` | Build or CI |
| `perf` | Performance |

## Examples

```
feat(web): add create_entry MCP tool
fix(db): align embedding vector dimensions with migration
docs: document local docker workflow
chore(docker): add pgadmin service
chore: initial project scaffold
```

## Do not

- Vague subjects: `update`, `fix stuff`, `wip`
- Past tense: `added feature` → use `add feature`
- Mix unrelated changes in one commit
